The paper deals with trajectory forecasting from visual sources, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a spatio-temporal convolutional neural network model, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper deals with robotics and autonomous systems, which falls under the category of robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses probability distributions, which is a topic in artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category.
